<p><b>Maria Montessori</b> (August 31, 1870 – May 6, 1952) was an <a href="/wiki/Italy" title="Italy">Italian</a> physician, educator, philosopher, humanitarian and devout <a href="/wiki/Catholicism" title="Catholicism">Catholic</a>; she is best known for her philosophy and the <a href="/wiki/Montessori_method" title="Montessori method">Montessori method of education</a> of children from birth to adolescence. Her educational method is in use today in a number of public as well as private schools throughout the world.</p>
